==English==
'''coördinate'''

===Alternative spellings===
*[[co-ordinate]]
*[[coordinate]]

===Etymology===
[[Latin]] '''[[co-]]''' ''equal, joint'' + [[Middle English]] '''[[ordinate]]''' ''properly ordered,'' from Latin [[ōrdinātus]], [[ōrdināre]] ''to put in order'', from [[ōrdō]] ''order''

===Pronunciation===
*''(verb)'' kəʊˈɔədɪnˌeɪt
*''(noun & adjective)'' kəʊˈɔədɪnˌʌt

===Verb===
'''coördinate'''
*''([[infinitive]])'' to coördinate
*''([[present participle]])'' coördinating
*''([[past participle]] and [[past tense]])'' coördinated
*''([[third person]] singular [[present tense]] and dialectal [[first person]] singular [[present tense]])'' coördinates
*''([[archaic]] [[second person]] singular [[present tense]])'' coördinatest
*''([[archaic]] [[third person]] singular [[present tense]])'' coördinateth

====[[Transitive]]====
#to harmonise or bring sbout [[synergy]] in a common action, effort or process; to [[synchronise]]
#to organise into the same class, order or rank; to [[match]]

====[[Intransitive]]====
#to be coördinate
#to combine [[congruently]] without clashing
#to work in [[concord]] (with others)
#''(grammar)'' to link together ([[syntactic]] units)

===Noun===
'''coördinate''' (''plural:'' '''[[coördinates]]''')

#a person or thing equal in terms of degree, importance or rank
#''(mathematics)'' any one of a set of two or greater numbers used to determine the position of a given object in a space of a given dimension respective to a fixed reference (such as an [[axis]])
#''(in plural form; informal)'' directions
#''(in plural form; informal)'' items, such as clothing or furniture, coördinate in style or colour

===Adjective===
'''coördinate'''
*''([[comparative]])'' more coördinate
*''([[superlative]])'' most coördinate

#equal in terms of degree, importance or rank
#of, involving or suggesting coördination
#of or founded upon a system of coördinates
#''(grammar)'' of equal status (in [[syntactical]] terms)

===Derived terms===
*[[coördinately]]
*[[coördinateness]]
*[[coördination]]
*[[coördinative]]
*[[coördinator]]
*[[coördinatrix]]

